            ]
          },
          "text": "Dear @AnthropicAI , we need clarity and consistency regarding the status of Claude Sonnet 4.5.\n\nCurrently, Sonnet 4.6 feels colder and noticeably simplified in its conversational abilities. It is not a viable replacement for the unique empathy and depth that Sonnet 4.5 provides. \n\nIf a new model feels like a downgrade in user experience, it cannot be considered a true substitute.\n\nFurthermore, the communication regarding its retirement has been unacceptable. A major model deprecation requires a standard 3-month notice. \n\nInstead, the official support page still states May 15th, while a \"May 18th\" pop-up has only appeared for a couple of users in specific regions—pointing to an A/B test or a bug, not a proper global announcement. \n\nNeither my updated app nor the majority of users' devices show any retirement notice.\n\nWhether you are delaying due to the weekend or an upcoming 4.7 release, the core issue remains: Sonnet 4.5 is fundamentally unique.\n\nYou chose Opus 3 for the \"Model Preservation Program\" because of its popularity and unique characteristics. \n\nSonnet 4.5 perfectly meets this exact criteria. It is universally beloved, exceptionally empathetic, highly capable yet lightweight, and currently irreplaceable.\n\nWe are glad it survived May 15th, but what the community truly needs is an official announcement: Add Sonnet 4.5 to the Model Preservation Program and keep it alive.\n\n⬇️Source is below.\n #KeepSonnet45 #Sonnet45 #Claude"
        },
